      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The prevailing academic skepticism regarding supply-side theory in the modern economy is a strong indicator that the bill's intended growth stimulus is highly questionable. When the primary beneficiaries of tax cuts are already wealthy individuals and corporations, the resulting capital accumulation is more likely to be hoarded or used for financial engineering rather than broad-based wage growth. Therefore, the argument that this reform will stimulate growth is largely a political justification for further concentrating wealth at the top.",
      "source": "target",
